entries.meaning: (of a country, geographical region, etc.) Surrounded by land (having no borders with the sea).
examples: Switzerland is landlocked and obviously will never be a great sea power and must always trade overland.

entries.meaning: Living in freshwater, such as landlocked salmon.
(US, real estate, of a property or parcel) Surrounded by other property and having no access to a public road.
